📊 Learning Report — 25 & 26 March 2026

🧠 Summary

- Total Trades: 24
- Wins: 13
- Losses: 11
- Win Rate: ~54%
- Bankroll: 1000 → 1043.37
- Return: +4.34%

---

📍 Market Insights

1. Strong Performance on "BETWEEN" Markets (BUY_NO)

- Most profitable trades came from:
  - BUY_NO
  - BUY_NO_STRONG
- Especially effective when:
  - AI probability is very low
  - Market overprices YES

👉 Insight:

«BETWEEN markets are often mispriced → strong edge on NO side»

---

2. Weakness on Some BUY_YES Trades

- Several losses came from:
  - BUY_YES
  - BUY_YES_STRONG
- Especially when:
  - threshold too aggressive (e.g. <65, >72)

👉 Insight:

«BUY_YES requires higher confidence threshold»

---

3. Temperature Clustering Effect

Observed:

- Temps often fall near mid-range (e.g. 70–75)

Impact:

- BETWEEN ranges close to actual temp are dangerous
- Far ranges = safer BUY_NO

👉 Insight:

«Avoid mid-range BETWEEN zones»

---

4. Risk Model Stability

- Fixed risk (2–3%) worked well
- No large drawdowns
- Smooth bankroll growth

👉 Insight:

«Risk model is stable → keep current sizing»

---

📊 City Observations

🌆 Los Angeles

- Stable temperatures
- Good performance on BUY_NO BETWEEN

🏙️ New York

- More volatility
- BUY_YES less reliable

🌇 Chicago

- Extreme ranges easier to exploit
- Strong BUY_NO performance

---

⚠️ Mistakes Identified

- Some trades taken outside optimal date window
- Tracker formatting errors (fixed)
- Missing early bankroll updates (fixed)

---

🚀 Strategy Improvements

Immediate

- Focus more on:
  - BUY_NO_STRONG
  - low AI probability setups

Avoid

- Weak BUY_YES signals
- BETWEEN near expected temperature

---

🔮 Next Steps

- Continue data collection (target: 100+ trades)
- Analyze:
  - PnL per strategy type
  - PnL per city
  - Edge vs outcome correlation

---

🧠 Key Learning

«Profitability comes from small consistent edges, not high win rates.»

«The system shows early signs of positive expectancy.»

